I"x<p>Canvas is a cloud-based platform that streamlines all of the digital tools and content required for a more connected learning experience.</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>More of its features (e.g. <a href="https://community.canvaslms.com/docs/DOC-10256-4152719640">Peer Review</a>, <a href="https://community.canvaslms.com/docs/DOC-13039-415264224">Group Discussions</a>, <a href="https://community.canvaslms.com/docs/DOC-10107-415254248">Group Assignments</a> may be used during the transition.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Instructors may utilize the PDF markup features of Canvas to provide feedback. Make sure to take the time to review the feedback.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Submission comments may be a good way to communicate with your instructor.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Make sure to submit your work as optimized files and/or as required by your instructor.</p>
  </li>
</ul>

